Cell.Data: Gameplay: Chatter while idle in town
I can barely get her to speak. Itâs as though the fog is still there, surrounding her and shrouding her view of the world.
I look into her eyes and nothingness stares back. I don't know what to do.
I - I'm so sorryâ¦ It's been hard. I don't think anyone has properly recovered. Everything feels a little quieter. Even those who escaped it find it difficult to talk about.
I hated every second of it, you know. Sending those refugees away during the Svriir crisisâ¦ I don't know how everyone just seems to forget it ever happened.
You need to put it behind youâ¦ We had no other choice, there was no room for themâ¦
You really think that? If we cared enough, we would have made room.
I - I remember seeing this boy, barely in his teens. He was sitting there beneath all the flailing limbs and the raised voices.
Just sitting there, eyes open, unblinking - as though the entire world had ceased to mean anything.
Then the crowd shiftedâ¦ I never saw him after that.
And how, may I ask, have you come by such information?
Aw, come on. We've always had our suspicions. Is it really that hard to believe?
It is not a question of whether I believe it or notâ¦ we should be above such gossip, and deal only with what we can see before us.
Bah, you're such a bore. If tales of incest fail to invite your curiosity, then there's no hope for you at all.
If that's how you feel, then perhaps we should cease having these conversations.
Mohabi! You got that new sword for me?
New sword? Are you sure, my friend? Why would you be in need of a new sword?
Just hand it over, will you? I might have slowed down a bit, but don't think for a second that I won't swing it in your direction.
There's no need for such threats, my friend. Mohabi is just concerned for your health, is that not what friends are for?
Sure, now take your coin, and try not to choke on itâ¦
No need to worry, my friend. Mohabi is always sensible with his coin.
You heard about the new Regent? Some of their exploits?
Yeah, some of it. It can't all be true, though, can it? There's no way one person, one human person, could do all that and come away alive.
Don't you think they would have announced that to the world by now? Wouldn't you, if you were a god?
Maybe. But gods think differently â they serve a higher purpose.
Have you ever heard a story about a god? They're as petty as we are! Always squabbling, tearing each other apart and ruining the world for everybody elseâ¦
Hmmm, I don't know. The gods I've heard about always seemed pretty selfless.
Don't know what gods you've been hearing aboutâ¦
I still don't understand it. Stormfall, the Jewel of the Sea, and with no war fleet to speak of.
And the greatest of all of them, The Radiant Armada, sent by Damaskus to fight someone else's warâ¦
Your son left with them, didn't he? How long has it been?
I - I don't knowâ¦ a long timeâ¦ I wonder if he even knows what's happened here while he's been gone.
Unlikely, I suppose â he and his crew have their own battles to fightâ¦
Yesâ¦ But they should have been fighting for Stormfall, not some random warlord on the edge of nowhere.
Perhaps not, but Stormfall always needs coin, perhaps now more than ever.
I - you're right, of course. I just can't stand itâ¦ I don't even know if he's alive â I could be waiting for a ghost.
I know, I knowâ¦ come on, let's go for a walk.
I heard your daughter was chosen?
Chosen? No, noâ¦ her name was drawn from the lotâ¦
What? No! It is the sworn duty of all in House Longshore to offer a child to the Blind Monks of MorkaÃ¯.
But you will miss her, will you not? Her entire life â devoted to walking blindly through the desert.
Well, Iâ¦ let's just say this: what if no-one did it? You know that only the blind can make it through the salt desert. Our caravans need our monks to survive the trip.
You are right, of course, I did not mean to offendâ¦
That scientistâ¦ Demetra, I think her name is? She's always doing something, tinkering with some device â her head lodged in some contraption or other.
Yesâ¦ come to think of it, not a day goes by where I don't see sparks flying.
Mark my words, she's going to blow a massive hole in the city one day.
I don't doubt it â I think I'll keep my distance from now on.
Not great. He's living somewhere in the lower ring these days, barely a rag to his name.
He had no family to go back to. He knew his fate as soon as the surgeon told him he was going to lose it.
I - I had no ideaâ¦ perhaps we should visit him? He always fought hard for us, had our backs â we owe him a few favours, and I could spare him some coin.
Yesâ¦ you're right, come get me when your shift ends, we'll see what we can do.
How did â How did you...?
Aha, it's all in the wrist, my friend!
This game is stupid, I'm sure you're cheating.
Aw, come now, give it another try. Remember, you have to skim it off the table and into the bucket, not straight into the bucket.
Yeah â you told me last time.
Well, come on then, throw the damn thing.
It was a long time coming, you know. Damaskus had his priorities wrong.
What do you mean by that?
He was always looking to undermine the authority of the great Houses. He forgot it was us who gave him his position in the first place.
So, why do we have someone like that at all? A Merchant-Prince? And now a Regent? Why not just have the Council rule?
Well, decisions would never be made if there was no one to have the final say. Every house has its vested interests, and it is almost impossible to compromise with so much to untangle.
With a regent making the final decisions, at least they have to provide compelling arguments for the motions they put forward.
I guess that makes senseâ¦ in a wayâ¦
Don't you ever get tired of robbing people blind with these âdealsâ of yours?
Robbing is not something I would ever do, you must have mistaken me with someone elseâ¦
Oh, come on, Mohabi, most of your buyers know nothing of the stuff you usher into their palms, never mind their true valueâ¦
Perhaps, but I cannot be blamed for another's ignorance, no?
Well, no, but don't you feel some sort ofâ¦ I don't know â moral imperative?
It dependsâ¦ many of my clients are noblesâ¦
Hi thereâ¦ you left, didnât you? You should probably get caught upâ¦
Ah, youâre back in Stormfallâ¦ well donât ask me about whatâs been going on, Iâve barely looked up from my lab!
Hm, what? Oh, itâs youâ¦ welcome backâ¦ Iâm probably the wrong person to ask about recent developmentsâ¦
The city has been a veritable hive of activity while you were gone, my friend.
Ah, youâve returned! The city has been growing â Mohabi has a sense for such things.
I hope your trip brought you plenty of coinâ¦ if you need to spend it, come to Mohabi first, yes?
{Mylord|Mylady}, there have been some developments in your absence, perhaps you should take a look.
Welcome back, {Mylord|Mylady}, Stormfallâs recent developments are ready for review.
Good to have you back, there have been some developments while you were gone.
Oh, hiâ¦ have you been somewhere? You look a little roughâ¦
I mean, Iâm sure something happened while you were goneâ¦ what that is? I couldnât tell you.
Back in Stormfall, I see. You should probably catch up with all the stuff thatâs been happening.
Welcome to the Diamond Council. Here we will focus on pressing matters â like ordering the construction of new infrastructure that will allow our enterprises to thrive...
Roads, workshops, defences... Irrigation networks... Anything like that â
No, no â not particularly â
Get used to this manoeuvring {Mylord|Mylady}. Valense is of House Blacktide, a house that invests heavily in agriculture, and sells a lot of produce beyond our borders.
So you see, everyone here wants something from you. Be sure to watch your step.
Do not play coy, Valense, you cannot â
{Excuse me, but are there any other urgent matters you wish to discuss?|Excuse me, but are there any other urgent matters you wish to discuss?}
{Then we shall adjourn the Council. I will recall you when I have need of guidance.|Then we shall adjourn the Council. I will recall you when I have need of guidance.}
Welcome back, {Mylord|Mylady}, is there anything you wish to discuss?
Ah, you have returned. Do you require our guidance?
The Champion returns, perhaps now we can make some decisions.
There you are, {Mylord|Mylady}, we were just discussing some projects we had in mind. Care to hear about them?
{Mylord|Mylady}! Do you have something for us?
Annaruz, would you stop, that will never â Oh, {Mylord|Mylady}, I did not see you enter. Was there something you needed?
Please, go ahead, {Mylord|Mylady}, we anxiously await your instruction.
So good of you to grace us with your presence, {Mylord|Mylady}. There are some matters to discuss, I believe?
Ah, we have been waiting for your return, {Mylord|Mylady}! Now, shall we begin?
Hello, {Mylord|Mylady}. I will assemble the Council at once.
Excuse me, {Mylord|Mylady}? In these times of uncertainty, Stormfall requires a firm guiding hand. Perhaps we should set aside the daydreaming for now.
I know you have a lot on your mind... please feel free to share it with the rest of us.
If you would like to be alone, {Mylord|Mylady}, do let us know.
Do let us know if you need to rest. We understand, of course; the duties of a Regent can be quite tiresome.
Iâm sure there is something we can discuss. Whatever you want, even the weather! Not so great at the moment, I must say. I suppose itâs called Stormfall for a reason.
You know, I donât ever remember it being this quiet in here.
Um, so, if thereâs nothing left to discuss... perhaps the Council should adjourn for now?
Is something the matter, {Mylord|Mylady}? You seem awfully quiet...
We will make the necessary arrangements.
Our workers will get to it at once, {Mylord|Mylady}.
As you wish, {Mylord|Mylady}, we will pass on your orders.
We will have our workers mobilized within the hour.
A sensible project, {Mylord|Mylady}, we will put some people on it as soon as possible.
Certainly, {Mylord|Mylady}, I will organize a workforce to handle the project.
Allow me to mobilize the work-force, {Mylord|Mylady}.
Our workers have toiled, and now Stormfall will reap the rewards. Take a look, {Mylord|Mylady}.
The workforce has acquitted itself brilliantly, {Mylord|Mylady}. Please, observe the results for yourself.
Work concluded, and to a high standard, might I add.
{Mylord|Mylady}, it seems our workers have reached the final milestone in their project.
Our workers have finished their project successfully, {Mylord|Mylady}. Let us review...
Work was difficult, but it is to be expected... come, behold the fruits of their labour.
Work has ended on the latest project, {Mylord|Mylady}, shall we inspect?
Greetings, {Mylord|Mylady}. The Council would like to discuss a very delicate matter with you.
{Is that so? Iâm all ears.|Is that so? Iâm all ears.}
After Damaskus was removed from power, the Houses agreed that Anankis should be excavated and its wealth claimed by Stormfall.
It was going well, for the most part, until our excavationists fell upon a strange artefact. They referred to it as âThe Ark of Anankis.'
Not long after we received their report, a fraction of the number we sent down there returned, eyes glazed over, mumbling words that meant nothing to anyone.
One of them had it, this supposed âArk,' in her tunic. We would not risk the same fate as the others, so we buried it in a cave network accessible only from the sea.
Iâve never seen them like this before, {Mylord|Mylady}. I hear no disdain or trickery in their voices. This thing scared them, thatâs for certain.
It could be otherworldly in nature... Although we cannot be sure, we thought we should tell you.
Given your affinity to such things, we thought you may be able to resist the effect it had on the others. However, if it is truly as powerful as it seems â
We would need some assurances first.
You would give us your oath. Firstly, that you will use the artefact to advance the interests of Stormfall and its Houses, and never to harm them. Secondly...
You will pay us handsomely for our retrieval efforts.
{I see... Thank you for bringing this to my attention.|I see... Thank you for bringing this to my attention.}
Of course, anything for the Champion of Stormfall.
{Mylord|Mylady}, the Anankis artefact has been retrieved. We have placed it in a secure container, ready for your viewing.
Excuse me, {Mylord|Mylady}? The artefact has already been returned.
Were you not informed? The Ark of Anankis has been retrieved.
Hmmm? Oh! {Mylord|Mylady}. Apologies, I was merely wondering what it would be like to gaze upon something so powerful. Probably best not to know.
Sorry, {Mylord|Mylady}... Was there something else? Please summon the Council in the palace if there is â we will be happy to advise.
The excursion has returned, {Mylord|Mylady}, there is nothing left for us to discuss here.
Iâm confused. Do you need to look at it again? Or are you hoping that by staring at it something new will suddenly happen?
{Mylord|Mylady}, you are aware of Stormfallâs Seekers, are you not?
{Doesnât ring a bell, no.|Doesnât ring a bell, no.}
They are, or were, a garrison of individuals devoted to the exploration of the continent.
But since tragedy has struck Stormfall, many of the Seekers have passed, and the garrison they once called home is a pile of rubble.
I suggest that that we rebuild the garrison, and have someone... worldly, shall we say, advising them.
In the absence of a senior Seeker, I suggest that we hire this âDashing Eugeneâ as an advisor. During his youth, Eugene travelled far and wide for the Purple Phoenix.
You see, Eugene has collected a wealth of tales... tales which could guide our Seekers to the rarest of treasures. Think about how profitable such treasures would be for Stormfall...
Oh stop, Annaruz, we all know who stands to gain the most from this arrangement. But please, do grovel some more...
Annaruz is of House Brightgale, {Mylord|Mylady}, and they are not doing as well.
They had an agreement with the Seekers you see, where they would provide House Brightgale with the most valuable and exotic of goods to trade.
Do not listen to Tabbitha, {Mylord|Mylady}... She, uh... Ah! Eugene, why donât you go ahead and say your piece?
Huh? Oh, right, thatâs my cue...
{Mylord|Mylady}, while I canât completely abandon my post at the Purple Phoenix, I canât stand the way they look at me, how they care so little for the stories Iâve gathered over the years.
And so I thought, if the Purple Phoenix doesnât want to take advantage of these tales of mine... who else do I know that could make use of them?
Iâm not asking for much â just for the odd coin to trickle my way, perhaps... Iâll guide your captains, send them to the right spots...
Be careful, {Mylord|Mylady}, Eugeneâs not the malicious sort, but he wouldnât be doing this if there wasnât something in it for him...
... It would be perfect for all involved.
{That remains to be seen... Weâll give it some thought.|That remains to be seen... Weâll give it some thought.}
The new Seekerâs Garrison is up and running. Plenty of eager new recruits ready to die finding treasures for Stormfall.
Back for more? Happy to be of service...
Oh, hey there. I was just telling this youngân a tale from the glory days, perhaps youâd like to hear it?
Plenty of eager Seekers waiting for your word. I almost wish I was going with them...
Oh, Seeker expeditions? I thought you were here for that other thing I do...
Where you thinking of sending the Seekers today? Somewhere dangerous, by any chance?
Hmm, wha â what? Ah, itâs you â was just resting my eyes. So, what will it be?
Are you looking for me? Course you are â got plenty of expeditions to choose from.
What do you wa â woah, sorry, {Mylord|Mylady}, where are you sending the Seekers, then?
Sorry, just assumed you were here to fund some expeditions. Guess I was wrong...
Might not be my place, but, uh, you think we could speed this along? Plenty to do, you see.
Got to say, I thought thereâd be more action involved...not that I would ever suggest you werenât a person of action... never mind...
{Mylord|Mylady}? I still work for the Purple Phoenix, and thereâs always paperwork to do... What am I saying? Take as long as you need!
What? Are you asleep? Iâve heard some people sleep with their eyes open; never thought Iâd see it for myself, though.
Come on then, shall we get this show on the road or what?
What are we waiting for? Something important?
Itâs not easy working two jobs â maybe come back when youâve got something for me.
Should be simple, donât expect anything too spectacular though.
Shouldnât cause them too much trouble.
Theyâll be back before you know it.
There? Well, alright, at least itâll be fairly easy for them.
Safe choice... although, thereâs something to be said for risk taking...
Ah, yes, sometimes itâs best to play it safe.
Sure, thatâll work. It will be a nice warm up for the more dangerous adventures I have in mind.
Not the most risky venture, but if thatâs where you want them to go...
Donât see them having much of a problem with this one...
Sure, seems doable, letâs see how they get on.
I guess thatâs not such a bad idea â not the most dangerous place in the world.
Itâll require sharp wits and a sharper blade, but I think theyâll manage.
They might hit a few bumps on the way, but they can handle it... hopefully.
May be a few hiccups, but I give them a solid chance of making it back.
No problem... well, not for me. For them? Perhaps just a little.
Alright, off they go, should get something good from this one...
Might be a bit of a stretch. Nasty place, that... But theyâre in with a shot.
Now thatâs what Iâm talking about. Oh, you might lose a few Seekers, sure, but the treasures awaiting them there â thereâs nowhere else like it.
Thereâs a lot of risk involved, and I mean a lot â but if anyone can pull it off, itâs Stormfallâs Seekers.
This is what theyâre trained for, right? Exploring the most perilous of places, and all of it in the pursuit of treasure...
Thereâll be a few bloody noses after this one... perhaps the odd lost limb... bold move, {Mylord|Mylady} â I like it.
Itâs not the easiest of routes... one of the most deadly, in fact... but that wonât stop Stormfallâs Seekers.
You know, just imagining the peril theyâre about to endure â brings back fine memories.
So, um, an expedition has returned. Whatâs left of them, at least...
That expedition has returned. Think they had a bit of trouble. Canât remember what the lad said â something about a slaughter, being the only survivor? No, that canât be it...
Somethingâs not right... they left with ten, and here I count... two? No, I think that counts as a half... Oh...
Not a pretty sight, {Mylord|Mylady}. Just the one horse, and whatâs left of a Seeker...
Some Seekers made it back... without treasure, though. Was too dangerous, they said.
Seekers have returned... not a pretty sight, I got to say.
Seekers are back... they donât have much to show for it, but theyâre back â I suppose thatâs a good thing.
Here we are, a successful expedition, all in all. Your Seekers have got something to show you.
Seekers have returned, safe and sound. More treasure to fill Stormfallâs coffers.
Now this is a real bounty... Huh? Oh, sorry, {Mylord|Mylady}. Please, come see for yourself...
Seekers are here â got a good haul by the looks of it..
Seekers are back. Letâs see what they managed to find...
Expedition was a success â fancy leavinâ some of those for me? No? Course, was only joking around...
A successful expedition, all in all. Some Seekers here with some treasures to show you.
{Mylord|Mylady}, as we are expanding Stormfall, the Council have been discussing how important it may be to have a vault to protect the cityâs wealth â
And your loyal friend Mohabi has been chosen for the job...
Uh, yes, we believe âyour loyal friendâ to be the perfect candidate for overseeing such an operation.
It will be the finest vault Stormfall has ever seen, and Mohabi will be its king.
Well, no, you will not be a âking.' You will âoverseeâ its construction and day-to-day operations, but it is not yours to do with as you wish.
Yes, yes, Mohabi understands... And for you, my friend â
And for you, â{Mylord|Mylady}â, Mohabi will build a personal vault, for all your personal treasures. A good deal, yes?
{Well, Iâm certainly intrigued. Weâll be sure to let you know.|Well, Iâm certainly intrigued. Weâll be sure to let you know.}
Of course, Mohabi will be waiting for your word... my friend.
Hello again, my friend. Your new vault is ready. It is truly a marvel. Come to me if you would like to make a deposit.
The expansion to your vault has been completed. You will be able to store far more equipment now... You are lucky Mohabi is your friend, wouldnât you agree?
Mohabi has been waiting for you... something to deposit?
Welcome, welcome... here to shed some of that extra weight you are carrying?
Mohabi, at your service... will you need access to your vault today?
Ah, youâre back! Do you have goods you would like to deposit?
My friend... you are always welcome here â what can I do for you?
Ah, yes, what is it you need from Mohabi this time?
As much as Mohabi enjoys your company, perhaps I could return to my other duties...
Sorry, my friend, do you still require my assistance?
Mohabi waits... patiently... for your word.
I understand your inaction, sometimes the diamonds steal away all sense of time, even from Mohabi.
You like your vault, I see? Would you like to deposit something?
Even in times of peace, it is best to be doing something, no?
If there is nothing, my friend, perhaps we should part ways â you know Mohabi is a busy man.
Excuse me... yes, Iâm talking to you, my friend. Mohabi would like a word if your schedule allows...
{Oh... I suppose I can spare the time... what is it?|Oh... I suppose I can spare the time... what is it?}
Youâre always looking for an edge in combat, yes?
And sometimes, to procure the best equipment, one must look beyond the âusual channels.â You understand?
I speak of The Dark Market, of course, a place where even the rarest of items can be bought. Some dealers even claim to have access to items that many would consider... legendary.
{Interesting, and where would I find such dealers?|Interesting, and where would I find such dealers?}
Ah, you see, you, my friend, would not find them at all. Mohabi will do that for you. It will take time, and a lot of coin, but I will find the contacts you need.
At first, I would find someone for crafting materials and reagents.
After that, it will cost more time, and more coin to find additional contacts for a more expansive range of items. But we may discuss that another time, perhaps.
{Sounds a little shady, but if you think itâs a good ideaâ¦|Sounds a little shady, but if you think itâs a good ideaâ¦}
Oh, but of course... and donât worry, the items we procure will be used for good, no? We would never let them fall into the hands of those who mean ill...
I have established our first contact in the Dark Market. Do visit when you wish to procure some crafting reagents; I will order my contact to begin searching right away.
I have secured another contact, my friend. He deals in all manner of rare equipment, so if you wish to find a rarer version of something you own, Mohabi can do that for you.
Another contact secured by your friend Mohabi! This one is willing to trade your equipment for a higher-quality version of it. I hope that pleases you.
My search was successful. If you like, my new contact is willing to trade your crafting materials for versions said to be of a more legendary nature.
Stop by at any time. Mohabi is always eager to serve.
Ah, welcome. Was there something you wished me to find?
My contacts are waiting for your word.
The Dark Market? Never heard of it, ha... sorry, my friend â what was it you needed?
What can I do for you today? Perhaps something from the Dark Market?
Greetings. Do you have any... delicate matters for Mohabi to attend to?
Come in, thereâs no need to be shy. We go way back, no?
What do you wish my contacts to find for you this time, my friend?
You are welcome here. Ahahaâ¦ Now, The Dark Market, was it?
You should not linger too long. Some might think we are... conspiring.
Perhaps we could complete this transaction soon, my friend, Mohabi has other enterprises he must attend to.
If there is nothing, may I return to my other customers?
It is a beautiful day, donât you think? Maybe we could complete our business and enjoy it â what do you say?
You are Mohabiâs most valued customer â but not his only customer, you understand?
My friend... you are a busy person, are you not? Perhaps it is not my services you require...
What are you looking at? Do Mohabiâs services not interest you?
Your reagent is ready to collect.
My contact has found the reagent you were looking for, take a look.
I have managed to acquire that reagent you ordered. Please, take it, my friend.
I have secured the reagent, just as you asked..
A new reagent is yours to collect.
And so the Dark Market providesâ¦
Mohabi has done just as you asked â a new reagent is ready to collect.
My contact has procured your rare equipment, my friend.
Mohabi has secured your new, rarer item.
Time to collect â your equipment may look the same, but this iteration is much harder to come by, believe me.
Mohabi has found your rare equipment. Come see.
I have procured the equipment in the rarity you asked for, my friend.
It was not easy to find, but a rarer version of your equipment is now in my possession.
Your equipment is ready, now as a far rarer iteration.
Just as you requested, Mohabiâs contact has found a rarer version of your equipment.
Ah, come look at what Mohabi has found for you. It is of much greater quality, I assure you.
As requested, my friend: the same item, but of greater quality.
When you are ready, I have your new, higher-quality equipment, secured and ready to collect.
Mohabi has found the equipment you wanted, my friend â its quality is far greater than your last.
A far superior item, procured and ready to collect.
An item of far greater quality, I must say. Please, collect when you are ready.
My contact was able to find the equipment you wanted... it is of far greater quality than your last, of course.
Your legendary reagent has been uncovered.
It may have been difficult, but now you have your reagent. Legendary, as you requested.
Mohabi has procured your legendary reagent, my friend.
Come, your legendary reagent is ready for you.
I have your legendary reagent, my friend.
Your legendary reagent â ready to collect. When has Mohabi ever failed you?
Your legendary reagent is now ready to collect.
As you requested. Your legendary reagent is ready for you.
Greetings, {Mylord|Mylady}. I have a renovation project that may be of interest to you.
I used to organize security details for many of Damaskusâ diplomats before... Well, before he, uh, ârelinquishedâ his throne...
Anyway, as I was about to say... Stormfall not so long ago had a Trade Assembly; it was used to organize diplomatic missions, as well as dispatch them.
If we were to renovate the assembly, our diplomats would have their base of operations returned to them.
You would be able to order trade missions to all over the continent.
They would leave in caravans, protected by a small detachment of Thunderblades. I would be on hand to brief them, of course.
{Trade will certainly be important if Stormfall is to rise again.|Trade will certainly be important if Stormfall is to rise again.}
Very good. Come to me when youâre ready to divert the necessary resources, {Mylord|Mylady}.
{Mylord|Mylady}, renovation works on the Trade Assembly have finished. Our diplomats have several trade missions planned â they are awaiting your authorization.
Welcome to the Assembly, {Mylord|Mylady}. Our diplomats have been awaiting your instruction.
There are a number of missions being considered. Take a look when youâre ready.
There you are! Our diplomats are becoming restless, perhaps you have a mission for them?
Greetings, {Mylord|Mylady}, there are caravans standing by. Give the word and Iâll prepare a security detail.
Oh, itâs you, {Mylord|Mylady}. There are plenty of missions prepared, just give the order.
Plenty of missions for you to peruse, {Mylord|Mylady}.
